Encryption 
$ gpg -c filename    #output is filename.gpg
$ gpg-zip -c -o newDirName dirName   #output is newDirName

Decryption 
$ gpg filename.gpg     #for file filename.gpg  
$ gpg-zip -d newDirName  #output is dirName

CCrypt 
sudo apt-get install ccrypt 
ccrypt filename 
ccrypt -d filename 

Rename 
$ mv filename newName   #renaming single file 
$ rename 's/^extra/Pre_/' *.mp4   #removing extra and adding Pre_ prefix to all files with .mp4 extention
$ rename 's/.webm/.mp4/' *.webm   #removing .webm and appending .mp4 suffix to all files with .webm extention

Zipping 
$ tar -cvf newname.tar directory      #zip -r
$ tar -xvf file.tar            #unzip 
$ tree directory   

